commits.message:
Enhanced ApiResponse DTO and created supporting Message/Enum classes for COBOL migration

- Updated ApiResponse.java to fix enum organization issues for Java compliance
- Created MessageLevel.java enum with INFO, WARNING, ERROR levels mapping to BMS color coding
- Created ResponseStatus.java enum with SUCCESS, ERROR states for CICS transaction equivalents
- Created comprehensive Message.java DTO with MessageLevel support and field-level validation
- All DTOs follow COBOL-to-Java migration patterns for CICS transaction processing
- Supports generic response wrapper with status tracking, messages list, and session updates
- Maps CICS COMMAREA functionality through sessionUpdates for session management
- Maintains functional parity with mainframe BMS message handling patterns
- All 11 comprehensive unit tests pass (100% success rate)
- Zero compilation errors, all classes compile successfully with Java 21
- Full Spring Boot 3.x integration support with Jackson annotations

issue.title: Getting real card parameters and using them in Javascript Templates
issue.body:
Hello. 
In the case when some card parameters are set as a percentage (for example, the width or height of the card), the actual parameters will vary depending on the device parameters (in particular, the display resolution) and the browser used. 
For example, there may be a situation in which the card will have a larger width (in pixels) on one device, and a smaller one on the other. But the width of a text box containing, for example, the name of an entity will be the same in both cases. 
Let's say the width of this text box is less than the width of the card on the first device, but it is larger than the width of the card on the second device.
Respectively, on the first device the entity name will be displayed in full, but not on the second. 
I would like to be able (in the case described above) to get the real width of the card on the device and the real width of the text box containing the name of the entity, be able to compare them, and also use the comparison result in Javascript Templates.
For example, for the second case, it would be possible to assign word wrapping to a new line, reduce the font size, or arrange automatic horizontal scrolling of the text. But the most important thing is that all these additional activities should only take place when the width of the text box is larger than the width of the card. That is, for example, I do not need automatic horizontal scrolling of the text or font size reduction in the event that it already fits completely on the card.
To organize what I described above, I apparently need to get the real width values inside Javascript Templates. 
More generally, access to more card parameters (as well as its composite and nested elements) inside Javascript Templates is desirable. 
Is there even such a possibility? Or maybe it can be provided in future versions?

comment.body:
@dcapslock,
> then think about reflowing the buttons so that they stack rather than quish

As far as I understand, the Home Assistant dashboards themselves, in accordance with some specific rules, determine the number of columns for placing cards, depending on the available width. Apparently, we have a more "flexible" situation when using the Sections layout, but there are still some rules that may change the number of columns when the available width is reached... To be honest, I don't really like the idea of moving the buttons to a new row (in some situations, it may disrupt the logic of their placement based on their functionality), and it's not always possible... So, as far as I understand, I can only provide for the use of the "scroll" described above in cases where the width of the cards decreases when the dashboard's content is "rebuilt" in case of available width - and using css, this works perfectly in all situations!
> Without knowing your whole config its hard to provide an example.

I don't have this configuration anymore either, as the css works perfectly when the sidebar's state changes... My question was about how this could help in a situation where the css is not being used (my initial solution). However, it now has only theoretical significance, as there is an easier and more effective solution available... 
> Overall, think about how CSS provides for what you need, not a state machine that you need to track.

Thank you so much for your help and clarification, and I will try to delve deeper into the possibilities provided by css whenever possible!

pull_request.title: feat(kv): rebuild user index after update
pull_request.body:
## Summary
- rebuild user KV index after updating entries
- cover userKV endpoint with tests for index rebuild and safe userId extraction

## Testing
- `npm run lint`
- `npm test` *(fails: SyntaxError: The requested module './app.js' does not provide an export named 'ensureFreshDailyIntake', etc.)*

issue.title: Copilot vscode extension exhaust GitHub API request limit.
issue.body:
<!-- Please search existing issues to avoid creating duplicates -->
<!-- Please attach logs to help us diagnose your issue -->

- Copilot Chat Extension Version: 0.30.1
- VS Code Version: 1.103.1 (Universal)
- OS Version: MacOS 10.5
- Feature (e.g. agent/edit/ask mode): None
- Selected model (e.g. GPT 4.1, Claude 3.7 Sonnet): Claude 4.0 Sonnet, GPT 5
- Logs:

```
"code_scanning_upload": {
    "limit": 5000,
    "used": 1029,
    "remaining": 3971,
    "reset": 1755443661
},
```

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Open vscode with any code folder.
2. Enable Copilot extension.
3. Check the rate limit from `https://api.github.com/rate_limit` 
4. It fires 10 code scanning update request per second in an idle vscode instance.
5. The requests didn't shown in vscode dev tool console or network tab.
6. This quickly exhaust the GitHub API 5000 requests per hour limit if I open multiple projects.
7.  This dramatically affect my work, cannot interact with GitHub just 10-15 mins after the limit reset.

issue.title: Issues trying to do supabase start, supabase pull and other commands locally
issue.body:
I've been unable to do supabase start or supabase pull of my project, failing with docker issues. The core issue seems to stem from this:

```
This is the acutal error I get WARNING:  invalid configuration parameter name "supautils.extension_custom_scripts_path", removing it
DETAIL:  "supautils" is now a reserved prefix.
psql: error: /docker-entrypoint-initdb.d/init-scripts/99-roles.sql: No such file or directory
[directory] container is not ready: unhealthy
```

The crash report id is `c0a5e6cc8e61429989ec501b82c01786`

I've not foudn the way to modify "supautils.extension_custom_scripts_path" or similar in the remote instance.

comment.body:
Temporary fix I have gotten so far.
find out the name of your container for postgres using 
`docker ps`

Then connect to it. (mine was supabase_db_ekko)
`docker exec -it supabase_db_ekko sh`

You will now have a terminal inside the postgres container. take a look at the config. 
`cat /etc/postgresql-custom/supautils.conf`

You will see the problematic line
supautils.extension_custom_scripts_path = '/etc/postgresql-custom/extension-custom-scripts'
That is what we wanna delete. 

I counted mine to be on line 10, so i deleted it using "sed" . since theres no nano or vim in the container, you can find your own way to edit the file to delete that line. 
`sed -i '10d' /etc/postgresql-custom/supautils.conf`

That command deleted line 10 from the file. 
I then reset my local supabase db

`supabase db reset`

Error is gone for now, it will return if I run supabase stop.

comment.body:
Creating a QApplication instance automatically in a component module can cause issues in testing and application lifecycle management. This should be handled by the main application entry point.

# NOTE: Requires a QApplication to be created before using QWidget-based classes.

issue.title: Critical: Trigram index panics on Unicode content during string slicing
issue.body:
## ğŸ› Bug Report

### Description
The trigram index crashes with a panic when processing Unicode content due to unsafe string slicing at byte boundaries that don't respect UTF-8 character boundaries.

### Error Details
```
thread 'main' panicked at src/trigram_index.rs:653:46:
byte index 497 is not a char boundary; it is inside 'ä¸­' (bytes 496..499)
```

### Location
File: `src/trigram_index.rs:653`
Code: `format!("{} ...", &content_str[..497])`

### Root Cause
The code attempts to slice a string at a fixed byte position (497) for creating a content preview, but this position may fall in the middle of a multi-byte UTF-8 character. When the content contains Unicode characters like Chinese text 'ä¸­', the slice operation panics.

### Impact
- **Severity**: CRITICAL - Causes complete application crash
- **Affected Operations**: 
  - Git repository ingestion fails
  - Any document insertion with Unicode content fails
  - Database becomes unusable for international content

### Reproduction Steps
1. Create a document with Unicode content (Chinese, emoji, etc.)
2. Try to insert it into KotaDB
3. Application panics at trigram index insertion

### Discovery Method
Found during dogfooding validation while ingesting KotaDB's own codebase, which contains Unicode test files (`tests/unicode_handling_test.rs`).

### Suggested Fix
Use proper UTF-8 aware string slicing:
```rust
// Instead of:
format!("{} ...", &content_str[..497])

// Use char_indices to find safe boundary:
let truncate_at = content_str.char_indices()
    .take(497)  // Take first 497 chars
    .last()
    .map(|(i, _)| i)
    .unwrap_or(content_str.len());
format!("{} ...", &content_str[..truncate_at])
```

### Related
- `tests/unicode_handling_test.rs` - Contains Unicode test cases that trigger this bug
- Issue #106 mentioned in the test file about Unicode handling

### Priority
This is a **CRITICAL** bug that completely breaks Unicode support and makes KotaDB unusable for international content.

### Validation Note
This issue was discovered through continuous dogfooding validation (Issue #214), demonstrating the value of testing KotaDB on its own codebase.

The changes implement static import cycle detection, service layer patterns, and improved import management across the GUI, tools, and database layers. issue.title: Copilot vscode extension exhaust GitHub API request limit.
issue.body:
<!-- Please search existing issues to avoid creating duplicates -->
<!-- Please attach logs to help us diagnose your issue -->

- Copilot Chat Extension Version: 0.30.1
- VS Code Version: 1.103.1 (Universal)
- OS Version: MacOS 10.5
- Feature (e.g. agent/edit/ask mode): None
- Selected model (e.g. GPT 4.1, Claude 3.7 Sonnet): Claude 4.0 Sonnet, GPT 5
- Logs:

```
"code_scanning_upload": {
    "limit": 5000,
    "used": 1029,
    "remaining": 3971,
    "reset": 1755443661
},
```

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Open vscode with any code folder.
2. Enable Copilot extension.
3. Check the rate limit from `https://api.github.com/rate_limit` 
4. It fires 10 code scanning update request per second in an idle vscode instance.
5. The requests didn't shown in vscode dev tool console or network tab.
6. This quickly exhaust the GitHub API 5000 requests per hour limit if I open multiple projects.
7.  This dramatically affect my work, cannot interact with GitHub just 10-15 mins after the limit reset.

pull_request.body:
Bumps [jest](https://github.com/jestjs/jest/tree/HEAD/packages/jest) and [@types/jest](https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/tree/HEAD/types/jest). These dependencies needed to be updated together. Updates `jest` from 29.7.0 to 30.0.5
Release notes

Sourced from jest's releases.

30.0.2

What's Changed

Fixes

  • [jest-matcher-utils] Make 'deepCyclicCopyObject' safer by setting descriptors to a null-prototype object (#15689)
  • [jest-util] Make garbage collection protection property writable (#15689)

Full Changelog: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md

Jest 30.0.1

What's Changed

Features

  • [jest-resolver] Implement the defaultAsyncResolver (#15679)

Fixes

  • [jest-resolver] Resolve builtin modules correctly (#15683)
  • [jest-environment-node, jest-util] Avoid setting globals cleanup protection symbol when feature is off (#15684)

Chore & Maintenance

  • [*] Remove and deprecate jest-repl package (#15673)
  • [jest-resolver] Replace custom isBuiltinModule with node's isBuiltin (#15685)

New Contributors

  • @â€‹vovkasm made their first contribution in jestjs/jest#15687

Full Changelog: https://github.com/jestjs/jest/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md

Jest 30

Today we are happy to announce the release of Jest 30. This release features a substantial number of changes, fixes, and improvements. While it is one of the largest major releases of Jest ever, we admit that three years for a major release is too long. In the future, we are aiming to make more frequent major releases to keep Jest great for the next decade.

If you want to skip all the news and just get going, run npm install jest@^30.0.0 and follow the migration guide: Upgrading from Jest 29 to 30.

Read the full blog post

Features

  • [*] Renamed globalsCleanupMode to globalsCleanup and --waitNextEventLoopTurnForUnhandledRejectionEvents to --waitForUnhandledRejections
  • [expect] Add ArrayOf asymmetric matcher for validating array elements. (#15567)
  • [babel-jest] Add option excludeJestPreset to allow opting out of babel-preset-jest (#15164)
  • [expect] Revert #15038 to fix expect(fn).toHaveBeenCalledWith(expect.objectContaining(...)) when there are multiple calls (#15508)
  • [jest-circus, jest-cli, jest-config] Add waitNextEventLoopTurnForUnhandledRejectionEvents flag to minimise performance impact of correct detection of unhandled promise rejections introduced in #14315 (#14681)
  • [jest-circus] Add a waitBeforeRetry option to jest.retryTimes (#14738)
  • [jest-circus] Add a retryImmediately option to jest.retryTimes (#14696)
  • [jest-circus, jest-jasmine2] Allow setupFilesAfterEnv to export an async function (#10962)
  • [jest-circus, jest-test-result] Add startedAt timestamp in TestCaseResultObject within onTestCaseResult (#15145)

... (truncated)

Sourced from jest's changelog.

30.0.5

Features

  • [jest-config] Allow testMatch to take a string value
  • [jest-worker] Let workerIdleMemoryLimit accept 0 to always restart worker child processes

Fixes

  • [expect] Fix bigint error (#15702)

30.0.4

Features

  • [expect] The Inverse type is now exported (#15714)
  • [expect] feat: support async functions in toBe (#15704)

Fixes

  • [jest] jest --onlyFailures --listTests now correctly lists only failed tests (#15700)
  • [jest-snapshot] Handle line endings in snapshots (#15708)

pull_request.body:
Bumps [cross-env](https://github.com/kentcdodds/cross-env) from 7.0.3 to 10.0.0.
Release notes

Sourced from cross-env's releases.

v10.0.0

10.0.0 (2025-07-25)

TL;DR: You should probably not have to change anything if:

  • You're using a modern maintained version of Node.js (v20+ is tested)
  • You're only using the CLI (most of you are as that's the intended purpose)

In this release (which should have been v8 except I had some issues with automated releases ğŸ™ˆ), I've updated all the things and modernized the package. This happened in #261

Was this needed? Not really, but I just thought it'd be fun to modernize this package.

Here's the highlights of what was done.

  • Replace Jest with Vitest for testing
  • Convert all source files from .js to .ts with proper TypeScript types
  • Use zshy for ESM-only builds (removes CJS support)
  • Adopt @â€‹epic-web/config for TypeScript, ESLint, and Prettier
  • Update to Node.js >=20 requirement
  • Remove kcd-scripts dependency
  • Add comprehensive e2e tests with GitHub Actions matrix testing
  • Update GitHub workflow with caching and cross-platform testing
  • Modernize documentation and remove outdated sections
  • Update all dependencies to latest versions
  • Add proper TypeScript declarations and exports

The tool maintains its original functionality while being completely modernized with the latest tooling and best practices

BREAKING CHANGES

  • This is a major rewrite that changes the module format from CommonJS to ESM-only. The package now requires Node.js >=20 and only exports ESM modules (not relevant in most cases).

pull_request.title: Add sparkle icon to WebUI component library
pull_request.body:
This PR adds a new `SparkleIcon` component to the WebUI icon library, implementing the sparkle icon design provided in the issue.

## Changes Made

- **Created SparkleIcon component** following the established icon patterns in the codebase
- **Added proper file structure** with `/components/Icon/src/assets/sparkle/` containing:
  - `Small.tsx` - The main icon component with the provided SVG path
  - `index.ts` - Export file for the `SparkleIcon`
- **Updated main assets index** to include the sparkle icon export for automatic library inclusion
- **Added test coverage** to ensure the icon renders without errors
- **Maintained code quality** by following existing TypeScript, ESLint, and Prettier standards

## Implementation Details

The SparkleIcon follows the same patterns as other icons in the library:
- Supports dynamic `size` and `color` props through the `IconColorProp` type
- Uses the `resolveIconColor` utility for consistent theming
- Default size of 24px with 20x20 viewBox matching the provided design
- Exports as `SparkleIcon` for consistent naming conventions

## Visual Result

The sparkle icon is now available in the component library and displays correctly in Storybook:

![SparkleIcon in Storybook](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/43e6ec8e-07cd-4664-8a34-79de4c145607)

The icon appears alphabetically positioned in the icon gallery and can be imported and used like any other icon in the library:

```tsx
import { SparkleIcon } from '@hautechai/webui.icon';

// Usage
<SparkleIcon size={20} color="actions.primary" />
```

Fixes #109.

issue.title: MMEX 1.9.0 is not opening in Ubuntu 24.04 with AMD processor
issue.body:
MMEX version:
 - [ ] 1.7.0
 - [ ] 1.8.0
 - [ ] 1.8.1
 - [ ] 1.8.2
 - [x] 1.9.0
 - [ ] Other (please specify)

Note: bug reporters are expected to have verified the bug still exists
either in the last stable version of MMEX or on updated development code
(master branch).

Operating System:
 - [ ] Windows
 - [ ] Mac OSX
 - [X] Linux 

# Description of the bug
After upgrading to 1.9.0, I am unable to open the mmex. My machine is on Ubuntu 24.04 and processor is AMD. When I tried to open the Money Manger, it just throws this error message on the screen "random_device: rdrand failed".  After searching in the internet, seems like this will happen only on AMD processor and some problem with Random number generation. 

# Reproduction

Is the bug reproducible? 
 - [x] Always 
 - [ ] Randomly 
 - [ ] Happened only once

Reproduction steps:
In 
Distributor ID:	Ubuntu
Description:	Ubuntu 24.04.2 LTS
Release:	24.04
Codename:	noble

processor      AMD Ryzen 5 5600X 6-Core Processor

Install Money Manager 1.9.0 and Open it.

Expected result:
It should open and show the last opened file

Actual result:
A pop up with error message "random_device: rdrand failed" is coming

# Additional information

If you have a backtrace for a crash or a warning, paste it here.

comment.body:
> Here is the crash file with details.
> 
> [mmes_crash.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/20995366/mmes_crash.txt)

Sorry for the late answer.

From mmes_crash.txt:
"model name	: AMD Ryzen 5 5600X 6-Core Processor"
looks like an old processor (November 2020).

This seems to be a bug with the random number described here:
https://gromacs.bioexcel.eu/t/failing-testes-in-gromacs-2020-6-and-2021-2-with-ryzen9-5950x/2172/2
and here:
https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=100444

The solution seems to be to update the BIOS, see here:
https://github.com/sass/node-sass/issues/3047

Further reading on this bug:
"A modern system needs high-quality pseudo-random numbers for lots of tasks, and the security implications of "random" meaning "always return0xFFFFFFFF" are difficult to predict."
https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2019/10/how-a-months-old-amd-microcode-bug-destroyed-my-weekend/
One can guess, that this bug has security implications.

@whalley I guess we can close this bug, since MMEX cannot do much here.

issue.title: Pico Display Base Board : keyboard on pico not recognized.
issue.body:
Hi,

I use the latest Pico Display Base Board 1.52 and a 73 TFT LCD 800x480 Ã©cran Tactile AVR STM32 Arm SSD1963 (from amazon.com.be).
I use a Raspberry Pi Pico.

At the beginning, the pico is no connected to the Pico Display Base Board.
I use a breadboard.
I put on the pico the picomite firmware PicoMiteRP2040USBV6.00.03.uf2.
5v power is given to the pico using the Vbus (pin 40) and Gnd (pin 38).
I can communicate with mmbasic using the UART on pin GP8 and GP9 like described in the picomite manual page 11.
I can also use the keyboard connected to the micro-usb port of the pico.
Here are the option used :
> option list
PicoMite MMBasic USB RP2040 Edition V6.00.03
OPTION SERIAL CONSOLE COM2,GP8,GP9
OPTION COLOURCODE ON
OPTION KEYBOARD FR, 0, 0, 150, 150
OPTION CPUSPEED (KHz) 200000
OPTION KEYBOARD REPEAT 150,150
>
At this point, I use picocom and a USB-TTL connector the communicate to mmbasic both ways (rx and tx). I can also use the connected keyboard to send commands to mmbasic. I see the results in the sdcreen of picocom.

The aim is to use the Pico Display Base Board.
So I connect the Raspberry Pi Pico to this board and connect the lcdpanel.
OPtion list gives the following : 
> option list
PicoMite MMBasic USB RP2040 Edition V6.00.03
OPTION SERIAL CONSOLE COM2,GP20,GP21
OPTION SYSTEM SPI GP10,GP11,GP12
OPTION SYSTEM I2C GP8,GP9
OPTION COLOURCODE ON
OPTION KEYBOARD FR, 0, 0, 150, 150
OPTION CPUSPEED (KHz) 200000
OPTION LCDPANEL CONSOLE
OPTION DISPLAY 40, 100
OPTION LCDPANEL SSD1963_7, LANDSCAPE
OPTION GUI CONTROLS 75
OPTION TOUCH GP18,GP19
GUI CALIBRATE 0, 3033, 0, 11011, 9223372036854775807
OPTION SDCARD GP22
OPTION KEYBOARD REPEAT 150,150
>

So everything is working good except that the keyboard connected to the pico is not recognized.

How can I resolve this issue ?

Thanks for the collaboration.

toone

comment.body:
toone

Thank you for purchasing the Pico Display board and your question.

I use the Base Board for multiple projects.  Though it's been a while since
I connected a keyboard to the PicoMite.
I will give your setup a try.  (Though you are connecting directly to the
USB-micro so no interference is possible from the board.)

Kevin
